<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Sesuvium verrucosum </i>is a native, perennial, succulent plant that forms extensive mats in saline or brackish, seasonal wetlands. Plants sprout from roots, or they may be effectively annuals, depending upon whether they experience periods of long-term inundation. The alliance occurs from central and southern California east to Missouri and south to Mexico (NatureServe 2007a). </div>
</div>

    
	
	
